<ul id="commtree_36514210"><li id="tree_36515110" class="comment oneline"><span class="ind"></span>
<div id="comment_status_36515110" class="commentstatus"></div>
<div id="comment_36515110" class="cw">
	<div id="comment_top_36515110" class="commentTop newcomment">
		<div class="title">
			<h4><a id="comment_link_36515110" name="comment_link_36515110" href="//yro.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=2256616&amp;cid=36515110" onclick="return D2.setFocusComment(36515110)" >Re:</a>


		 	<span id="comment_score_36515110" class="score"> (<a href="#" onclick="getModalPrefs('modcommentlog', 'Moderation Comment Log', 36515110); return false"><span class=opt>Score:</span>2</a>)</span></h4>
		</div>
		<div class="details">
			<span class="by"><span class="byby">by </span><a href="//slashdot.org/~CarsonChittom">CarsonChittom</a>  <span class="uid"><a href="//slashdot.org/~CarsonChittom">(2025388)</a></span></a></span><span class="writes" style="display:none"> writes:</span> 
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_36515110"></span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_36515110"><p><div class="quote"><p>You can't legally use your private currency to settle a debt or to pay your taxes </p></div><p>This is not quite right.  You <em>can</em> legally use it to settle a debt provided the other person/institution knows what it is (i.e., you are not defrauding them) and accepts it; on the other hand, they would be well within their rights to refuse and demand Federal Reserve Notes.  I believe it <em>would</em> be illegal (not just ineffective) to attempt to pay your taxes in a private currency.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_36515110">

